h3cNat.name: h3cNat

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

h3cNat.description: This MIB contains objects to manage configuration of NAT. There are no constraints on this MIB.

h3cNATClearSessionSlotNo.name: h3cNATClearSessionSlotNo
h3cNATClearSessionSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board in which administrator wants to clear data of the session. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it. This node only supports 'set' operation. The return value of 'get' operation is meaningless.

h3cNATBLConnectHighValue.name: h3cNATBLConnectHighValue
h3cNATBLConnectHighValue.description: The maximal connection amount. If the connection amount exceeds the value, the IP address will be added into blacklist. The IP address will not be removed from blacklist until the connection amount is less than the minimal connection amount.

h3cNATBLConnectHighRate.name: h3cNATBLConnectHighRate
h3cNATBLConnectHighRate.description: The maximal connection rate(in second). If the connection rate exceed the value, the IP address will be added into blacklist. The IP address will not be removed from blacklist until the connection rate is less than the minimal connection rate.

h3cNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate.name: h3cNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate
h3cNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate.description: The maximal special connection rate(in second). When administrator wants to control the speed of connection, he can selects the connection speed rate or special connection rate.

h3cNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate.name: h3cNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate
h3cNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate.description: The minimal special connection rate(in second).

h3cNATBLConnectSumEnable.name: h3cNATBLConnectSumEnable
h3cNATBLConnectSumEnable.description: Enable or disable the connection amount control.

h3cNATBLConnectRateEnable.name: h3cNATBLConnectRateEnable
h3cNATBLConnectRateEnable.description: Enable or disable the connection rate control.

h3cNATNPAgingTime.name: h3cNATNPAgingTime
h3cNATNPAgingTime.description: There are two kinds of aging time in NP. One is fast and the other is slow. Administrator can select one or other. The defalult is fast.

h3cNATPoolInfoTable.name: h3cNATPoolInfoTable
h3cNATPoolInfoTable.description: NAT address pool table : The address in the pool is the IP address in the global network. The pool can span 255 IP addresses.All address pools configured by administrator are recorded in this table.

h3cNATPoolInfoEntry.name: h3cNATPoolInfoEntry
h3cNATPoolInfoEntry.description: The entry of NAT address pool table.

h3cNATPoolIdx.name: h3cNATPoolIdx
h3cNATPoolIdx.description: Index of the address pool: The index uniquely indicates the address pool in the system, and its range is from 1 to 320.

h3cNATPoolStartIpAddr.name: h3cNATPoolStartIpAddr
h3cNATPoolStartIpAddr.description: The start IP address of address pool: It must be less than or equal to the end IP address.

h3cNATPoolEndIpAddr.name: h3cNATPoolEndIpAddr
h3cNATPoolEndIpAddr.description: The end IP address of address pool: It must be more than or equal to the start IP address.

h3cNATPoolSlotNo.name: h3cNATPoolSlotNo
h3cNATPoolSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board to which the address pool is bound. The address translation is processed by this NAT board . The relation between address pool and slotNo is n:1. When the address pool is not bound to the NAT board,the value is 255.

h3cNATPoolRefCounter.name: h3cNATPoolRefCounter
h3cNATPoolRefCounter.description: The counter of reference. A address pool can be associated with more than one ACL and the counter of reference is recorded in this field. When the address pool is not associated with ACL, the value is 0.

h3cNATPoolRowStatus.name: h3cNATPoolRowStatus
h3cNATPoolRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If h3cNATPoolIdx, h3cNATPoolStartIpAddr and h3cNATPoolEndIpAddr were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

h3cNATOutboundTable.name: h3cNATOutboundTable
h3cNATOutboundTable.description: NAT out bound table: through associating ACL number, address pool with NAT board, administrator can designate which inside IP address can be translated to global IP address in the pool and the translation is processed by which NAT board.

h3cNATOutboundEntry.name: h3cNATOutboundEntry
h3cNATOutboundEntry.description: The entry of NAT out bound table.

h3cNATOutboundAclNo.name: h3cNATOutboundAclNo
h3cNATOutboundAclNo.description: The number of ACL(Access Control List). When the packet accords with the rule in the ACL, its source IP address will be translated to IP address in Address pool.

h3cNATOutboundPoolIdx.name: h3cNATOutboundPoolIdx
h3cNATOutboundPoolIdx.description: The index of address pool in h3cNATPoolInfoTable. when administrator doesn't use the address pool and use the IP address of the interface as the address of global network, the value is 2147483647.

h3cNATOutboundIsNoPat.name: h3cNATOutboundIsNoPat
h3cNATOutboundIsNoPat.description: Whether to use no pat manner. The translation of no pat is that the translation doesn't use the port information of packet.

h3cNATOutboundSlotNo.name: h3cNATOutboundSlotNo
h3cNATOutboundSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

h3cNATOutboundRowStatus.name: h3cNATOutboundRowStatus
h3cNATOutboundRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If h3cNATOutboundAclNo or h3cNATOutboundAclNo and h3cNATOutboundPoolIdx were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

h3cNATServerTable.name: h3cNATServerTable
h3cNATServerTable.description: NAT inside Server Table. Administrator can configure server in the private network which can provide service for people in the public network. The translation map is : (InsideIP , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort ) (InsideIP + 1 , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort + 1) (InsideIP + 2 , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort + 2) ... ... ... (InsideIP+n(=InsideIP2),InsidePort--> GlobalIP,GlobalPort+n(=GlobalPort2))

h3cNATServerEntry.name: h3cNATServerEntry
h3cNATServerEntry.description: The entry of NAT inside server table.

h3cNATServerProType.name: h3cNATServerProType
h3cNATServerProType.description: The type of protocol: icmp(1), tcp(6), udp(17) and others.

h3cNATServerGlobalIP.name: h3cNATServerGlobalIP
h3cNATServerGlobalIP.description: The global IP address of Inside Server.

h3cNATServerStartGlobalPort.name: h3cNATServerStartGlobalPort
h3cNATServerStartGlobalPort.description: The start global port of Inside Server. When the port need not be configured, the value is 0.

h3cNATServerEndGlobalPort.name: h3cNATServerEndGlobalPort
h3cNATServerEndGlobalPort.description: The end global port of Inside Server. When administrator doesn't configure a series of inside server, the value is 0. If the value is not zero, the value of (GlobalPort2-GlobalPort) must be equal to (InsideIP2 - InsideIP).

h3cNATServerStartInsideIP.name: h3cNATServerStartInsideIP
h3cNATServerStartInsideIP.description: The start private IP address of Inside Server.

h3cNATServerEndInsideIP.name: h3cNATServerEndInsideIP
h3cNATServerEndInsideIP.description: The end private IP address of Inside Server. When administrator doesn't configure a series of inside server, the value is 0.0.0.0.

h3cNATServerInsidePort.name: h3cNATServerInsidePort
h3cNATServerInsidePort.description: The private port of Inside Server.

h3cNATServerSlotNo.name: h3cNATServerSlotNo
h3cNATServerSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

h3cNATServerAclNumber.name: h3cNATServerAclNumber
h3cNATServerAclNumber.description: Number of basic or advanced acl.

h3cNATServerRowStatus.name: h3cNATServerRowStatus
h3cNATServerRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If h3cNATServerProType, h3cNATServerGlobalIP, h3cNATServerGlobalPort and h3cNATServerInsideIP were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

h3cNATTimeOutTable.name: h3cNATTimeOutTable
h3cNATTimeOutTable.description: NAT Time out Table. When a connection is established, if there are not any actives in this connection between the time, it will be disconnected.

h3cNATTimeOutEntry.name: h3cNATTimeOutEntry
h3cNATTimeOutEntry.description: The entry of NAT Time out Table.

h3cNATBLEnableTable.name: h3cNATBLEnableTable
h3cNATBLEnableTable.description: NAT blacklist function Enable Table. In this table, administrator can decide whether to start the function of blacklist in the NAT board. When the function of blacklist can't be set for a NAT board, the number of NAT board is 256.

h3cNATBLEnableEntry.name: h3cNATBLEnableEntry
h3cNATBLEnableEntry.description: The entry of NAT blacklist Enable Table.

h3cNATBLEnableSlotNo.name: h3cNATBLEnableSlotNo
h3cNATBLEnableSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. When the function of blacklist can't be set for a NAT board, the value is 255.

h3cNATBLEnable.name: h3cNATBLEnable
h3cNATBLEnable.description: Start or stop of function of balcklist.

h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable.name: h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable
h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable.description: The table of connection control of special IP address. In this table, administrator can decide to adopt which manner to control the connection which IP address is the special IP address.

h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry.name: h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry
h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry.description: The entry of the table of connection control of special IP address.

h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP.name: h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP
h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP.description: The special IP address. The IP is private IP address.

h3cNATBLIPConnectHighValue.name: h3cNATBLIPConnectHighValue
h3cNATBLIPConnectHighValue.description: The maximal connection amount. It must be more than the minimal connection amount.

h3cNATBLIPConnectLowValue.name: h3cNATBLIPConnectLowValue
h3cNATBLIPConnectLowValue.description: The minimal connection amount. It must be less than the maximal connection amount.

h3cNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate.name: h3cNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate
h3cNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate.description: Whether to use the special connection rate control.

h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus.name: h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus
h3cNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If h3cNATBLIPConnectHighValue, h3cNATBLIPConnectLowValue and h3cNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

h3cNATBLManagerTable.name: h3cNATBLManagerTable
h3cNATBLManagerTable.description: The management table of blacklist. The table doesn't support 'getnext' operation.

h3cNATBLManagerEntry.name: h3cNATBLManagerEntry
h3cNATBLManagerEntry.description: The entry of management table of blacklist.

h3cNATBLIpAdress.name: h3cNATBLIpAdress
h3cNATBLIpAdress.description: The IP address of entry of blacklist.

h3cNATBLConSpd.name: h3cNATBLConSpd
h3cNATBLConSpd.description: The state of connection rate: red(1) : the connection rate is above the upper limit. yellow(2): the connection rate is between the upper and lower limit. green(3) : the conneciton rate is below the lower limit.

h3cNATStatTable.name: h3cNATStatTable
h3cNATStatTable.description: The statistics information table of NAT module.

h3cNATStatEntry.name: h3cNATStatEntry
h3cNATStatEntry.description: The entry of statistics information table of NAT module.

h3cNATStatNATBoardNo.name: h3cNATStatNATBoardNo
h3cNATStatNATBoardNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

h3cNATStatActiveTblCount.name: h3cNATStatActiveTblCount
h3cNATStatActiveTblCount.description: Active PAT session count In software.

h3cNATStatActiveTblCountInNP.name: h3cNATStatActiveTblCountInNP
h3cNATStatActiveTblCountInNP.description: Active PAT session count In NP.

h3cNATStatNumOfUsedPort.name: h3cNATStatNumOfUsedPort
h3cNATStatNumOfUsedPort.description: The number of used port in NP.

h3cNATStatNumOfGoodPkt.name: h3cNATStatNumOfGoodPkt
h3cNATStatNumOfGoodPkt.description: The number of good packet in NP.

h3cNATStatNumOfBadPkt.name: h3cNATStatNumOfBadPkt
h3cNATStatNumOfBadPkt.description: The number of bad packet in NP.

h3cNATSequenceSessionCount.name: h3cNATSequenceSessionCount
h3cNATSequenceSessionCount.description: Active session table count hash by private IP.

h3cNATSessionTable.name: h3cNATSessionTable
h3cNATSessionTable.description: The nat session information table. There is the address translation information in the table. The sketch map of connection is pc1(private Net)------------------>NAT Device ------------------>Server(public Net) InsideIP, InsidePort---->translating to GlobalIP, GlobalPort------>PeerIP, PeerPort.

h3cNATSessionEntry.name: h3cNATSessionEntry
h3cNATSessionEntry.description: The entry of session information table.

h3cNATSessionHashNumber.name: h3cNATSessionHashNumber
h3cNATSessionHashNumber.description: The row number of the hash table.

h3cNATStaticRowStatus.name: h3cNATStaticRowStatus
h3cNATStaticRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If h3cNATStaticInsideIp and h3cNATStaticGlobalIp were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

h3cNATStaticEnableTable.name: h3cNATStaticEnableTable
h3cNATStaticEnableTable.description: Active the static Nat on interface.

h3cNATStaticEnableEntry.name: h3cNATStaticEnableEntry
h3cNATStaticEnableEntry.description: Active the static Nat on interface.

h3cNATStaticEnable.name: h3cNATStaticEnable
h3cNATStaticEnable.description: Enable/disable the static Nat on the interface(h3cNatStaticEnableIfIndex). disable (0) enable (1)

h3cNATDnsMapTable.name: h3cNATDnsMapTable
h3cNATDnsMapTable.description: This table is used to set mapping of DNS.

h3cNATDnsMapProtocolType.name: h3cNATDnsMapProtocolType
h3cNATDnsMapProtocolType.description: TCP Transmission Control Protocol. UDP User Datagram Protocol.

h3cNATDnsMapLastUseTime.name: h3cNATDnsMapLastUseTime
h3cNATDnsMapLastUseTime.description: Its value is the time that the device uses from startup to last use 'Dns Map'record. If the value is 0,the device never use this record.

h3cNATDnsMapRowStatus.name: h3cNATDnsMapRowStatus
h3cNATDnsMapRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If h3cNATDnsMapDomainName, h3cNATDnsMapGlobalIp and h3cNATDnsMapGlobalPortor h3cNATDnsMapDomainName, h3cNATDnsMapGlobalIp, h3cNATDnsMapGlobalPort and h3cNATDnsMapProtocolType were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.
